Comment: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,EN,,0,0,0,,--------------------TEXT-EN--------------------
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.91,EN,,0,0,0,,So you are a women in the mid-18th century
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.91,0:00:04.99,EN,,0,0,0,,You are getting dressed and in order to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.99,0:00:07.46,EN,,0,0,0,,you put on your shift, your petticoat, your hoops
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.46,0:00:09.20,EN,,0,0,0,,because you feel like being, a bit posh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:11.27,EN,,0,0,0,,Your second petticoat, your stays, your pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.27,0:00:13.82,EN,,0,0,0,,your gown, your cap, fichu, ruffles, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:16.48,EN,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you are a woman in the mid-19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.48,0:00:17.80,EN,,0,0,0,,in which case you’ve got your chemise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.80,0:00:21.98,EN,,0,0,0,,your corset, crinoline, petticoat, skirt, bodice, shoes, shawls, and bonnet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.98,0:00:24.41,EN,,0,0,0,,Or maybe you’re an Elizabethan where instead you are opting for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.41,0:00:26.75,EN,,0,0,0,,smock, partlet, pair of bodies, roll, farthingale
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.75,0:00:29.70,EN,,0,0,0,,underskirt, overskirt, bodice, cap, and ruff
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.70,0:00:34.05,EN,,0,0,0,,The question looms eternally with all those layers interconnecting and overlapping
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.05,0:00:35.99,EN,,0,0,0,,especially around the waist area
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.99,0:00:40.09,EN,,0,0,0,,How did anyone get anything off efficiently to pee multiple times per day?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.09,0:00:43.85,EN,,0,0,0,,You’ll perhaps notice the one garment not included in your daily dressing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.85,0:00:45.29,EN,,0,0,0,,throughout any of these periods is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.29,0:00:47.96,EN,,0,0,0,,in fact, we today would think of as “underwear”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:50.10,EN,,0,0,0,,for this simple logical reason that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.10,0:00:52.22,EN,,0,0,0,,for the most part women just didn’t wear them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.22,0:00:53.64,EN,,0,0,0,,But for the sake of this video by the way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.64,0:00:57.41,EN,,0,0,0,,I’m going to referring to this particular garment as “underwear"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.56,EN,,0,0,0,,and not meaning the general concepts of garments
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.56,0:01:01.53,EN,,0,0,0,,that women wear underneath the closing since
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:03.94,EN,,0,0,0,,yes they did indeed wear many more things
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.94,0:01:06.01,EN,,0,0,0,,under their other things than we do today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.01,0:01:08.80,EN,,0,0,0,,But the word “pants” confuses the Americans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.80,0:01:10.55,EN,,0,0,0,,and “panties” confuses the British
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.55,0:01:13.09,EN,,0,0,0,,and any more obscure reference to said small clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.09,0:01:17.37,EN,,0,0,0,,is just generally unnecessarily unfair to our multilingual friends
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.37,0:01:19.22,EN,,0,0,0,,So underwear, it shall be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.22,0:01:21.64,EN,,0,0,0,,I say women “for the most part” didn’t I wear underwear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.64,0:01:24.24,EN,,0,0,0,,because as is the precarious way of history
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.24,0:01:26.12,EN,,0,0,0,,we are all just interpreting the selected evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.12,0:01:27.70,EN,,0,0,0,,that happens to survive to us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:31.98,EN,,0,0,0,,However, many centuries later and that subsequently there is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:34.30,EN,,0,0,0,,as a straightforward fact when speaking about things that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:36.77,EN,,0,0,0,,we have no firsthand experience in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.77,0:01:40.65,EN,,0,0,0,,And, well, this no underwear thing is where the evidence points us at present
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.65,0:01:43.47,EN,,0,0,0,,there will undoubtably be uncovered at some point in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.47,0:01:46.15,EN,,0,0,0,,Some evidence to suggest that one woman somewhere was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.15,0:01:49.43,EN,,0,0,0,,in fact, regularly wearing what we might call underwear today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:53.79,EN,,0,0,0,,There is for example the textile finds uncovered in Lengberg Castle in Austria
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.79,0:01:57.18,EN,,0,0,0,,including this pair of what distinctly looks to be underwear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.18,0:02:01.16,EN,,0,0,0,,and although confirmably similar in style to the undergarments worn by men
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.16,0:02:05.31,EN,,0,0,0,,in the circa-15th century period attributed as the date of origin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:08.47,EN,,0,0,0,,it was found amongst fragments of a distinctly women’s undergarment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:10.05,EN,,0,0,0,,So, anything is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.05,0:02:14.58,EN,,0,0,0,,But for the most part, evidence or the comparative lack of surviving evidence thereof
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.58,0:02:18.23,EN,,0,0,0,,and not just surviving garments but lack of written indications
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.23,0:02:21.17,EN,,0,0,0,,in journals, inventories, dictionaries, and wills
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.17,0:02:24.93,EN,,0,0,0,,indicates that for the most part, these garments were not a prevalent part of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.93,0:02:27.90,EN,,0,0,0,,the average woman’s wardrobe until about the 19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.90,0:02:28.86,EN,,0,0,0,,But we’ll get to that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:31.40,EN,,0,0,0,,When you think about it, it kind of make sense
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.40,0:02:34.56,EN,,0,0,0,,when you already got layers of shifts and petticoats and skirt’s going on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.56,0:02:36.07,EN,,0,0,0,,with the lower half of your outfit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:37.01,EN,,0,0,0,,who would have said,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:39.61,EN,,0,0,0,,“Hey, you know what would be a really great idea?”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.61,0:02:43.69,EN,,0,0,0,,And additional little garment that we have to surgically extract from under our skirts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:45.80,EN,,0,0,0,,and stays every time we have to pee
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.80,0:02:48.67,EN,,0,0,0,,It is far easier not to have extract anything at all
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.67,0:02:50.86,EN,,0,0,0,,but rather to just lift up your skirts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:53.88,EN,,0,0,0,,position your chamber pot accordingly and go
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.88,0:02:55.21,EN,,0,0,0,,“But wait!” I hear you ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.21,0:02:57.38,EN,,0,0,0,,“What was one supposed to do at that time of moon
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.38,0:03:00.71,EN,,0,0,0,,when one might actually prefer to have something a bit tighter going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.71,0:03:02.90,EN,,0,0,0,,despite the additional inconvenience?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:06.11,EN,,0,0,0,,References to 18th century menstrual management are rare
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.11,0:03:08.83,EN,,0,0,0,,save for the implication of an apron being used
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.83,0:03:11.11,EN,,0,0,0,,Abby Cox has experimented with a theory of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.11,0:03:14.85,EN,,0,0,0,,using an apron made of absorbent diaper woven cloth on her channel
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.85,0:03:17.92,EN,,0,0,0,,if you care to investigate in greater detail on this subject
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:20.02,EN,,0,0,0,,There are copious references and advertisements
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.02,0:03:22.92,EN,,0,0,0,,by the latter part of the 19th century for reusable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:25.88,EN,,0,0,0,,and later disposable towels that could be clipped to sanitary belts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:28.96,EN,,0,0,0,,and sanitary belts as well as absorbent aprons worn to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.33,EN,,0,0,0,,protect the back of the skirts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.33,0:03:33.27,EN,,0,0,0,,were prevalent in advertisements by the early 20th century
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.34,0:03:38.68,EN,,0,0,0,,The transition from no drawers to yes drawers is not one happens overnight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.68,0:03:42.45,EN,,0,0,0,,but is one that occurs gradually sometime around the 19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.54,EN,,0,0,0,,such that the Workwomen’s Guide states by 1838
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.54,0:03:46.98,EN,,0,0,0,,that drawers are, quote,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.98,0:03:51.75,EN,,0,0,0,,“worn by men, women, and children of all classes and almost all ages”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.60,EN,,0,0,0,,I should note that Queen Victoria ascended the English throne
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:56.76,EN,,0,0,0,,only one year before in 1837
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.76,0:04:00.33,EN,,0,0,0,,and drawers have already apparently become a ubiquitous necessity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.33,0:04:02.56,EN,,0,0,0,,according to the reference from 1838
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:06.82,EN,,0,0,0,,So we can’t necessarily blame delicate Victorian sensibilities for their adoption
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:09.38,EN,,0,0,0,,Visual representations of fashionable dress continue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.38,0:04:13.52,EN,,0,0,0,,to depict commando ladies all the way up until at least 1811
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:17.49,EN,,0,0,0,,But this image, dated a mere seven years later to 1818
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.49,0:04:19.46,EN,,0,0,0,,is already showing a woman wearing drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.46,0:04:21.80,EN,,0,0,0,,as part of her usual dressing routine
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:24.43,EN,,0,0,0,,Much like a change from the term stays to corset
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:27.38,EN,,0,0,0,,The adoption of drawers wasn’t a transition that happened over night
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.38,0:04:30.17,EN,,0,0,0,,but rather more likely over the course of a generation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.17,0:04:34.06,EN,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, despite the adoption of drawers under dresses in the 19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.06,0:04:36.53,EN,,0,0,0,,these still didn’t pose any impediment to peeing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:39.18,EN,,0,0,0,,as the vast majority of surviving examples
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:41.48,EN,,0,0,0,,the crotch seam of 19th century drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:44.59,EN,,0,0,0,,and later combinations was generally left open
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:48.12,EN,,0,0,0,,I say generally because there are examples of sewn drawers that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:51.37,EN,,0,0,0,,if museum dating can be trusted would have existed towards
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.37,0:04:54.53,EN,,0,0,0,,the mid to early part of the 19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.53,0:04:57.20,EN,,0,0,0,,well before sewn drawers became widespread
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:04:59.53,EN,,0,0,0,,But the circumstances in which these were worn
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.53,0:05:01.63,EN,,0,0,0,,whether by a staunchly anti-corset lady
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:04.39,EN,,0,0,0,,an invalid or just someone particularly committed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:07.13,EN,,0,0,0,,to completely undressing in order to pee is unknown
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.13,0:05:09.43,EN,,0,0,0,,And of course, it is also unconfirmable as to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:11.51,EN,,0,0,0,,whether or not these garments even were worn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.51,0:05:15.97,EN,,0,0,0,,considering that the ones that survive seem to be—surprisingly pristine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:19.85,EN,,0,0,0,,It is around the very end of 19th century and into the Edwardian era
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.85,0:05:22.21,EN,,0,0,0,,that we begin to see this seam being closed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:24.63,EN,,0,0,0,,first with buttons in some surviving examples
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.63,0:05:26.50,EN,,0,0,0,,so that the seam could still be opened easily
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:29.88,EN,,0,0,0,,without the entire garment needing to be extracted from under the corset
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.88,0:05:33.42,EN,,0,0,0,,and finally sewn up completely as we approach the 1920s
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.07,0:05:37.20,EN,,0,0,0,,The simplification and shortening of skirts
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:39.71,EN,,0,0,0,,and the adoption of the brassiere in place of the corset
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.71,0:05:42.35,EN,,0,0,0,,are likely significant factors in this evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:44.93,EN,,0,0,0,,since fewer foundation layers simultaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:47.52,EN,,0,0,0,,meant less layers of protection and concealment
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:51.69,EN,,0,0,0,,but also, easier potential for extraction of a pair of closed-seam underwear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.69,0:05:53.24,EN,,0,0,0,,at necessary moments
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:55.09,EN,,0,0,0,,The term of “pair of underwear”, by the way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.09,0:05:57.54,EN,,0,0,0,,comes from their ancestral pair of drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:06:00.40,EN,,0,0,0,,and the two individual legs from which they were comprised
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.40,0:06:04.54,EN,,0,0,0,,The prevalent adoption of underwear is thus a surprisingly recent event
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:08.85,EN,,0,0,0,,There is evidence of men’s underpants occurring throughout periods of history
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.85,0:06:11.39,EN,,0,0,0,,from the linen briefs of the medieval periods
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:14.86,EN,,0,0,0,,to the occasional evidence of linen drawers in the 18th century
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.86,0:06:19.06,EN,,0,0,0,,despite most visual evidence suggesting that drawers were likewise uncommon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:20.90,EN,,0,0,0,,in menswear by this time as well
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.90,0:06:23.65,EN,,0,0,0,,But this isn’t wholly irrelevant to the dilemma of peeing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:25.55,EN,,0,0,0,,since men’s style of dress were
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:27.07,EN,,0,0,0,,if not less layered
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:29.41,EN,,0,0,0,,at least constructed so that they were easily dismantlable
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.41,0:06:34.42,EN,,0,0,0,,for peeing purposes with codpieces, fall fronts and button flies
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.42,0:06:37.95,EN,,0,0,0,,So that was me sufficiently taking six whole minutes longer than it should have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:39.92,EN,,0,0,0,,to answer this exceedingly simple question
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:42.95,EN,,0,0,0,,but if you are not here for unnecessarily passionate explorations
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.95,0:06:46.82,EN,,0,0,0,,into the urinary habits of pre-20th century humans then honestly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:48.64,EN,,0,0,0,,I don’t even know why you’re still here
Comment: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,CN,,0,0,0,,--------------------TEXT-CN--------------------
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.91,CN,,0,0,0,,所以你是18世纪中叶的女性
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.91,0:00:04.99,CN,,0,0,0,,你在穿衣服，为了做到这一点
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.99,0:00:07.46,CN,,0,0,0,,你穿上你的衬衣，衬裙，发箍
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.46,0:00:09.20,CN,,0,0,0,,因为你觉得自己挺时髦
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.20,0:00:11.27,CN,,0,0,0,,您的第二件衬裙，您的胸衣，口袋
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.27,0:00:13.82,CN,,0,0,0,,您的礼服，帽子，绒毛，荷叶边等
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.82,0:00:16.48,CN,,0,0,0,,也许您是19世纪中叶的女性
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.48,0:00:17.80,CN,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下，你有自己的连衣裙
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.80,0:00:21.98,CN,,0,0,0,,您的紧身胸衣，短裙，衬裙，裙子，鞋子，披肩和帽子
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.98,0:00:24.41,CN,,0,0,0,,或者，也许您是伊丽莎白时期的人，而您却选择了
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.41,0:00:26.75,CN,,0,0,0,,罩衫，无袖衣，紧身衣，裙卷，裙撑
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.75,0:00:29.70,CN,,0,0,0,,短裙，超短裙，紧身胸衣，帽子和围脖
Dialogue: 1,0:00:29.70,0:00:34.05,CN,,0,0,0,,一层层的服饰交织覆盖，导致了一个永恒的问题
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.05,0:00:35.99,CN,,0,0,0,,特别是在腰部周围
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.99,0:00:40.09,CN,,0,0,0,,每天该怎么方便高效地脱衣服上厕所？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.09,0:00:43.85,CN,,0,0,0,,您可能会注意到日常穿着中未包括的一件衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.85,0:00:45.29,CN,,0,0,0,,它并未出现在之前的列举中
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.29,0:00:47.96,CN,,0,0,0,,实际上，我们如今称之为“内衣”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.96,0:00:50.10,CN,,0,0,0,,由于这个简单的逻辑原因
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.10,0:00:52.22,CN,,0,0,0,,在大多数情况下，女性只是不穿它们
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.22,0:00:53.64,CN,,0,0,0,,但是为了这个视频
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.64,0:00:57.41,CN,,0,0,0,,我将把这件特定的服装称为“内衣”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.56,CN,,0,0,0,,并不意味着我们平常所指的那种
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.56,0:01:01.53,CN,,0,0,0,,那些女性穿在其他衣服之内的衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.53,0:01:03.94,CN,,0,0,0,,是的，她们如今确实在其他衣服下
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.94,0:01:06.01,CN,,0,0,0,,多穿了很多东西
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.01,0:01:08.80,CN,,0,0,0,,但是“裤子”一词使美国人感到困惑
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.80,0:01:10.55,CN,,0,0,0,,和“内裤”使英国人困惑
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.55,0:01:13.09,CN,,0,0,0,,还有对这些小衣服的晦涩参考
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.09,0:01:17.37,CN,,0,0,0,,对我们多语种的朋友来说通常只是不必要地不公平
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.37,0:01:19.22,CN,,0,0,0,,所以，内衣应该是
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.22,0:01:21.64,CN,,0,0,0,,我说女人“大部分”不穿内衣
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.64,0:01:24.24,CN,,0,0,0,,因为这是不稳定的历史方式
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.24,0:01:26.12,CN,,0,0,0,,我们都在解释特定的证据
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.12,0:01:27.70,CN,,0,0,0,,碰巧能支持我们的观点
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.70,0:01:31.98,CN,,0,0,0,,但是，许多世纪以后，后来没有这种东西
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.98,0:01:34.30,CN,,0,0,0,,当谈到那些
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.30,0:01:36.77,CN,,0,0,0,,我们没有以下方面的第一手资料
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.77,0:01:40.65,CN,,0,0,0,,而且，不穿内衣的事，这是目前证据所体现的
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.65,0:01:43.47,CN,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问，将来某个时候会发现
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.47,0:01:46.15,CN,,0,0,0,,一些证据表明某些地方的女性
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.15,0:01:49.43,CN,,0,0,0,,实际上，经常穿我们如今称之为内衣的衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.43,0:01:53.79,CN,,0,0,0,,例如，在奥地利的Lengberg城堡中发现了纺织品
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.79,0:01:57.18,CN,,0,0,0,,包括这对看起来很像内衣的东西
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.18,0:02:01.16,CN,,0,0,0,,并且尽管在样式上肯定与男人穿着的内衣相似
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.16,0:02:05.31,CN,,0,0,0,,它起源于约15世纪时期
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.31,0:02:08.47,CN,,0,0,0,,是在明显的女性内衣的碎片中发现的
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.47,0:02:10.05,CN,,0,0,0,,所以，一切皆有可能
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.05,0:02:14.58,CN,,0,0,0,,但是在大多数情况下，还是比较缺乏现存的证据
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.58,0:02:18.23,CN,,0,0,0,,不单是遗留下来的服饰，而且缺乏书面资料
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.23,0:02:21.17,CN,,0,0,0,,在报纸，清单，字典和遗嘱中
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.17,0:02:24.93,CN,,0,0,0,,这表明通常来说，直到19世纪前
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.93,0:02:27.90,CN,,0,0,0,,这些服饰依然不太流行
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.90,0:02:28.86,CN,,0,0,0,,但是我们依然可以研究它
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.86,0:02:31.40,CN,,0,0,0,,试想一下
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.40,0:02:34.56,CN,,0,0,0,,当你已经有很多衣服，衬裙和裙子的时候
Dialogue: 1,0:02:34.56,0:02:36.07,CN,,0,0,0,,在你的下半身
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.07,0:02:37.01,CN,,0,0,0,,谁会说，
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.01,0:02:39.61,CN,,0,0,0,,“嘿，你知道什么是一个好主意吗？”
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.61,0:02:43.69,CN,,0,0,0,,还有我们必须通过像外科手术一样从裙子下提取的其他小衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.69,0:02:45.80,CN,,0,0,0,,并在每次必须尿尿时停留
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.80,0:02:48.67,CN,,0,0,0,,根本不提取任何东西要容易得多
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.67,0:02:50.86,CN,,0,0,0,,而是举起你的裙子
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.86,0:02:53.88,CN,,0,0,0,,相应地放置便壶并开始
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.88,0:02:55.21,CN,,0,0,0,,“可是等等！”我听你问
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.21,0:02:57.38,CN,,0,0,0,,“在来月经的时候应该做什么？
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.38,0:03:00.71,CN,,0,0,0,,当一个人实际上可能想穿更紧身一些的，
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.71,0:03:02.90,CN,,0,0,0,,尽管还有其他不便？”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.90,0:03:06.11,CN,,0,0,0,,很少有资料提及18世纪的月经管理
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.11,0:03:08.83,CN,,0,0,0,,除了使用围裙的含义
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.83,0:03:11.11,CN,,0,0,0,,艾比·考克斯在她的频道上尝试了以下理论
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.11,0:03:14.85,CN,,0,0,0,,使用由吸收性尿布编织布制成的围裙
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.85,0:03:17.92,CN,,0,0,0,,如果您想对此问题进行更详细的研究
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.92,0:03:20.02,CN,,0,0,0,,有大量的参考文献和广告显示
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.02,0:03:22.92,CN,,0,0,0,,到19世纪后期出现的重复利用和
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.92,0:03:25.88,CN,,0,0,0,,之后出现的可以夹在卫生带上的一次性毛巾
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.88,0:03:28.96,CN,,0,0,0,,和卫生带以及穿在身上的吸收性围裙
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.33,CN,,0,0,0,,来保护裙子的后部
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.33,0:03:33.27,CN,,0,0,0,,在20世纪初期流行于广告中
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.34,0:03:38.68,CN,,0,0,0,,从无裤子到有裤子的转变不是一朝一夕的事
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.68,0:03:42.45,CN,,0,0,0,,但是是在19世纪某个时候逐渐发生的一种
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.54,CN,,0,0,0,,例如《女企业家指南》在1838年之前
Dialogue: 1,0:03:45.54,0:03:46.98,CN,,0,0,0,,裤子据说是
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.98,0:03:51.75,CN,,0,0,0,,“所有年龄段，几乎所有年龄段的男人，女人和孩子都穿着”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.60,CN,,0,0,0,,我应该指出，维多利亚女王登上了英国王位
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.60,0:03:56.76,CN,,0,0,0,,仅在1837年之前的一年
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.76,0:04:00.33,CN,,0,0,0,,裤子显然已经成为普遍的必需品
Dialogue: 1,0:04:00.33,0:04:02.56,CN,,0,0,0,,根据1838年的参考资料
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.56,0:04:06.82,CN,,0,0,0,,因此，我们不一定会因采用维多利亚时代的精致感而受到指责
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.82,0:04:09.38,CN,,0,0,0,,时装的视觉表现继续
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.38,0:04:13.52,CN,,0,0,0,,描绘突击队女士直到1811年
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.52,0:04:17.49,CN,,0,0,0,,但是这张影像，距今仅七年，直到1818年
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.49,0:04:19.46,CN,,0,0,0,,已经显示出一个穿着裤子的女人
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.46,0:04:21.80,CN,,0,0,0,,作为她惯常的穿衣习惯的一部分
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.80,0:04:24.43,CN,,0,0,0,,很像保留词的变化
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.43,0:04:27.38,CN,,0,0,0,,裤子的采用并不是一夜发生的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.38,0:04:30.17,CN,,0,0,0,,但在一代人的过程中更有可能
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.17,0:04:34.06,CN,,0,0,0,,然而，尽管在19世纪采用了裤子在衣服下面
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.06,0:04:36.53,CN,,0,0,0,,这些仍然对小便没有任何阻碍
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.53,0:04:39.18,CN,,0,0,0,,作为大多数尚存的例子
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.18,0:04:41.48,CN,,0,0,0,,19世纪裤子的开缝
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.48,0:04:44.59,CN,,0,0,0,,后来的组合通常都处于开放状态
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.59,0:04:48.12,CN,,0,0,0,,我之所以这么说是因为有一些缝制裤子的例子
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.12,0:04:51.37,CN,,0,0,0,,如果博物馆标注的时间可靠的话
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.37,0:04:54.53,CN,,0,0,0,,十九世纪中叶
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.53,0:04:57.20,CN,,0,0,0,,缝制裤子流行之前
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.20,0:04:59.53,CN,,0,0,0,,但是这些衣服的穿着情况
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.53,0:05:01.63,CN,,0,0,0,,是否由坚定的紧身胸衣女士
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.63,0:05:04.39,CN,,0,0,0,,残疾人或只是特别犯案的人
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.39,0:05:07.13,CN,,0,0,0,,完全脱了衣服来小便是未知的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.13,0:05:09.43,CN,,0,0,0,,当然，对于
Dialogue: 1,0:05:09.43,0:05:11.51,CN,,0,0,0,,这些衣服是否穿过
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.51,0:05:15.97,CN,,0,0,0,,考虑到那些幸存者似乎是原始的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.25,0:05:19.85,CN,,0,0,0,,大约在19世纪末，进入爱德华时代
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.85,0:05:22.21,CN,,0,0,0,,我们开始看到这个接缝已经闭合
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.21,0:05:24.63,CN,,0,0,0,,首先在一些尚存的示例中使用按钮
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.63,0:05:26.50,CN,,0,0,0,,这样就可以轻松打开接缝
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.50,0:05:29.88,CN,,0,0,0,,无需从紧身胸衣下面抽出整件衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.88,0:05:33.42,CN,,0,0,0,,最终在我们接近19世纪20年代时被完全缝制
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.07,0:05:37.20,CN,,0,0,0,,裙子的简化和缩短
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.20,0:05:39.71,CN,,0,0,0,,并采用胸罩代替紧身胸衣
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.71,0:05:42.35,CN,,0,0,0,,可能是这一演变过程中的重要因素
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.35,0:05:44.93,CN,,0,0,0,,因为减少了打底的层次
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.93,0:05:47.52,CN,,0,0,0,,同时意味着更少的保护和隐蔽
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.52,0:05:51.69,CN,,0,0,0,,而且，更容易提取一条封闭缝内衣
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.69,0:05:53.24,CN,,0,0,0,,在必要的时候
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.24,0:05:55.09,CN,,0,0,0,,顺便说一下，“内衣”一词
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.09,0:05:57.54,CN,,0,0,0,,来自他们祖先的裤子
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.54,0:06:00.40,CN,,0,0,0,,和组成它们的两条腿
Dialogue: 1,0:06:00.40,0:06:04.54,CN,,0,0,0,,因此，普遍采用内衣是一个令人惊讶的近期事件
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.07,0:06:08.85,CN,,0,0,0,,有证据表明，男性内裤在整个历史时期都在发生
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.85,0:06:11.39,CN,,0,0,0,,从中世纪的亚麻内裤
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.39,0:06:14.86,CN,,0,0,0,,到18世纪偶尔出现的亚麻制裤子证据
Dialogue: 1,0:06:14.86,0:06:19.06,CN,,0,0,0,,尽管大多数视觉证据表明裤子同样罕见
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.06,0:06:20.90,CN,,0,0,0,,这次也穿男装
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.90,0:06:23.65,CN,,0,0,0,,但这与小便的困境并不完全无关
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.65,0:06:25.55,CN,,0,0,0,,因为男人的着装风格是
Dialogue: 1,0:06:25.55,0:06:27.07,CN,,0,0,0,,如果不少分层
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.07,0:06:29.41,CN,,0,0,0,,至少构造易于拆解
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.41,0:06:34.42,CN,,0,0,0,,搭配，前缀和纽扣蝇
Dialogue: 1,0:06:34.42,0:06:37.95,CN,,0,0,0,,所以我足够花整整六分钟的时间
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.95,0:06:39.92,CN,,0,0,0,,回答这个极其简单的问题
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.92,0:06:42.95,CN,,0,0,0,,但是如果您不在这里进行不必要的热情求知
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.95,0:06:46.82,CN,,0,0,0,,坦白讲讲20世纪前人类的小便习惯
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.82,0:06:48.64,CN,,0,0,0,,我甚至不知道你为什么还在这里
